Herb Ellis Meets Jimmy Giuffre: Herb Ellis Meets Jimmy Giuffre is an album by American jazz guitarist Herb Ellis and saxophonist, composer and arranger Jimmy Giuffre which was released on the Verve label in 1959.

Do Something to Me: Jimmy Wisner arranged the music for the song.

Come with Me (Puff Daddy &amp; Jimmy Pag: In the same year, Page played guitar for rap singer/producer Puff Daddy's song "Come with Me", which heavily samples Led Zeppelin's "Kashmir" and was included in the soundtrack of "Godzilla".
